Ecology. This species is encountered in undisturbed pristine forests (e.g. LS 4 ) and in moderately disturbed rural areas (CR 3 ;
Freitag 2005
), which suggests a rather high ecological potency. Most specimens of
Hydraena palawanensis
were collected in residual pools of a small stream, and between CPOM in sandy slack-water zones of small lowland streams. Additional material was retrieved from emergence traps positioned over pool sections of first to fourth order streams. Therefore it is likely that the species inhabits the detritus intersticial and avoids strong currents.
